Ten people have been convicted of carrying out armed attacks in Mozambique,  and sentenced to 40 years in prison. A number of other defendants got shorter sentences for lesser offences but most of the dozens of other defendants were found not guilty because of a lack of evidence. Militants have been carrying out beheadings and attacks on villages and defence targets in some districts of Cabo Delgado since October 2017. Terrorism: 8 sentenced to life for joining IS-linked group Egyptian court confirms Morsi’s death sentence Southern Africa in revolt: A journalist’s report shaped  Nigeria’s historic role (II)